Description: Fragment of sub-round handle rising to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine red-buff.
Production date: 137 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name, Thersandros. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0139.04. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1092)
